HEADWORD: Olla
<hw>Ol"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Olio</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pot or jar having a wide mouth;
a cinerary urn, especially one of baked clay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dish of stewed meat; an olio; an
olla-podrida.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Olla-podrida</ent>⟦br⟧
